  "response": "Here are some ways to test and potentially improve your IQ:\n\nIQ Testing Methods:\n1. Online IQ tests\n- Mensa official test\n- Professional IQ tests\n- Free online assessments (less accurate)\n\n2. Professional IQ tests\n- Administered by psychologists\n- More comprehensive and accurate\n- Examples: Wechsler Adult Intelligence Scale (WAIS)\n\nWays to potentially improve cognitive abilities:\n1. Mental exercises\n- Puzzles\n- Chess\n- Sudoku\n- Brain training apps\n- Memory games\n\n2. Learning new skills\n- Learn a new language\n- Play musical instruments\n- Take online courses\n- Read challenging books\n\n3. Lifestyle factors\n- Regular exercise\n- Healthy diet\n- Adequate sleep\n- Stress management\n- Meditation\n\n4. Cognitive training\n- Problem-solving activities\n- Critical thinking exercises\n- Learning complex subjects\n\n5. Continuous learning\n- Stay curious\n- Challenge yourself intellectually\n- Explore new topics\n\nImportant notes:\n- IQ is partially genetic\n- Not a comprehensive measure of intelligence\n- Multiple types of intelligence exist\n- Consistent practice can help cognitive development\n\nRemember, intelligence is multifaceted and can be developed through continuous learning and engaging activities.",
